    • Method Detail

      • getContactSubtypeFilter

        public java.lang.String[] getContactSubtypeFilter()
        Deprecated. 
        Get the Contact subtype security filter, which is an array of Contact type codes identifying subtypes that can NOT be viewed by the current user. Examples: To exclude the Doctor subtype, the array should contain only "Doctor". To exclude all PersonVendors, the array should include "PersonVendor" and its subtypes "Doctor" and "Attorney". When the user has the permission to see all subtypes of searchContactRootType, then the array is empty.
        Returns:
        an array of contact subtypes NOT viewable by the current user.

      • setContactSubtypeFilter

        public void setContactSubtypeFilter(java.lang.String[] subtypeFilter)
        Deprecated. 
        Get the Contact subtype security filter, which is an array of Contact type codes identifying subtypes that can NOT be viewed by the current user. Examples: To exclude the Doctor subtype, the array should contain only "Doctor". To exclude all PersonVendors, the array should include "PersonVendor" and its subtypes "Doctor" and "Attorney". When the user has the permission to see all subtypes of searchContactRootType, then the array is empty.
        Parameters:
        subtypeFilter - - an array of subtype relative names to filter out in the remote query
